The Speaker of the Nasarawa State House of Assembly,Alhaji Ibrahim Balarabe-Abdullahi, has urged politicians to play by the rules to ensure rancour-free elections in 2019. This is contained in his New Year message signed and issued by his Press Secretary, Jibrin Gwamna, in Keffi. Balarabe-Abdullahi expressed optimism that the forthcoming general elections would be peaceful if politicians played by the rules of the game. While felicitating with Nigerians on the New Year celebration, the speaker also urged them to pray fervently for the success of the general elections. â€œNigerians should intensify prayers so that the year will be the best ever witnessed so far and for the general elections to be peaceful and successful. He also described 2019 as a very significant year for all Nigerians as the people will be going to the polls to elect leaders at all levels. Balarabe-Abdullahi, who is also the National Vice Chairman, North Central of Nigeria Conference of Speakers of State Legislatures, enjoined Nigerians to actively participate in the elections. He further called on Nigerians to support and pray for leaders at all levels to enable them to succeed. He also urged the people of the state and Nigerians to be law abiding, respect constituted authorities and live peacefully with one another irrespective of their affiliations.(NAN)